{"id":8434,"date":"2018-08-08T18:15:20","date_gmt":"2018-08-08T12:45:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/?p=8434"},"modified":"2018-08-16T18:49:58","modified_gmt":"2018-08-16T13:19:58","slug":"dayalu-ammal","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/dayalu-ammal\/","title":{"rendered":"Dayalu Ammal Wiki, Age, Husband, Family, Biography &amp; More"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-8469\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal.jpg\" alt=\"Dayalu Ammal\" width=\"666\" height=\"438\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-300x197.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-768x505.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 666px) 100vw, 666px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong>Dayalu Ammal\u00a0<\/strong>is <strong>famous for being the Wife of Tamil Nadu\u2019s former Chief Minister and DMK Chief, M Karunanidhi.<\/strong>\u00a0She got married to Karunanidhi at a very young age, after the death of his first wife; becoming his second wife.\u00a0Check out Dayalu Ammal Wiki, Age, Husband, Childre, Family,\u00a0 Controversy, Biography &amp; More.<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_62 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Contents<\/p>\n<label for=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce3a8371ff\" class=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-label\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/label><input type=\"checkbox\"  id=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce3a8371ff\"  aria-label=\"Toggle\" \/><nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/dayalu-ammal\/#BiographyWiki\" title=\"Biography\/Wiki\">Biography\/Wiki<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/dayalu-ammal\/#Family_Husband\" title=\"Family, Husband\">Family, Husband<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/dayalu-ammal\/#Controversy\" title=\"Controversy\">Controversy<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/dayalu-ammal\/#SalaryNet_WorthMoney_Factor\" title=\"Salary\/Net Worth\/Money Factor\">Salary\/Net Worth\/Money Factor<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/dayalu-ammal\/#Facts\" title=\"Facts\">Facts<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"BiographyWiki\"><\/span><span id=\"BiographyWiki\" class=\"ez-toc-section\" style=\"color: #800080\">Biography\/Wiki<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>She is a <strong>86 years<\/strong> old widow of\u00a0M.\u00a0Karunanidhi. Born in the\u00a0Year 1936 in\u00a0Tamil Nadu, India.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_8470\" style=\"width: 672px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8470\" class=\"wp-image-8470 \" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Husband.jpg\" alt=\"Dayalu Ammal With Her Husband, M.\u00a0Karunanidhi\" width=\"662\" height=\"407\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Husband.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Husband-300x185.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Husband-768x472.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 662px) 100vw, 662px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-8470\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Dayalu Ammal With Her Husband, M.\u00a0Karunanidhi<\/p><\/div>\n<p>She is a businesswoman. She was just <strong>12 years<\/strong> old when she got married to\u00a0<strong>M.\u00a0Karunanidhi<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Family_Husband\"><\/span><span id=\"Family_Husband\" class=\"ez-toc-section\" style=\"color: #800080\">Family, Husband<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>In 1946, she tied the knot with\u00a0<strong>M.\u00a0Karunanidhi.\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_8471\" style=\"width: 459px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8471\" class=\"wp-image-8471 \" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Husband1.jpg\" alt=\"Dayalu Ammal With Her Husband, M.\u00a0Karunanidhi\" width=\"449\" height=\"553\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Husband1.jpg 480w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Husband1-244x300.jpg 244w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 449px) 100vw, 449px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-8471\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Dayalu Ammal With Her Husband, M.\u00a0Karunanidhi<\/p><\/div>\n<p>The couple was blessed with four children. She has 3 sons<b>:<\/b>\u00a0<strong>M. K. Alagiri<\/strong> (Politician),\u00a0<strong>M.K Stalin<\/strong>\u00a0(Politician), <strong>M. K. Tamilarasu<\/strong> (Producer)\u00a0and one daughter: <strong>Selvi Geetha Kovilam<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_8472\" style=\"width: 526px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8472\" class=\" wp-image-8472\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammals-Sons.jpg\" alt=\"Dayalu Ammal's Sons\" width=\"516\" height=\"391\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammals-Sons.jpg 443w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammals-Sons-300x228.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 516px) 100vw, 516px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-8472\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Dayalu Ammal&#8217;s Sons<\/p><\/div>\n<p>In the 1960s, Her happily married life was tormented when Karunanidhi got married to\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/rajathi-ammal\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Rajathi Ammal<\/a> in a secret ceremony. Though it was considered as an illegal marriage according to\u00a0the Hindu Marriage Act, 1955.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_8482\" style=\"width: 615px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8482\" class=\" wp-image-8482\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Karunanidhi-and-Rajathi-Ammal.jpg\" alt=\"Dayalu Ammal With Karunanidhi and Rajathi Ammal\" width=\"605\" height=\"363\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Karunanidhi-and-Rajathi-Ammal.jpg 448w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Karunanidhi-and-Rajathi-Ammal-300x180.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 605px) 100vw, 605px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-8482\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Dayalu Ammal With Karunanidhi and Rajathi Ammal<\/p><\/div>\n<p>Dayalu is the <strong>stepmother<\/strong> of <strong>M. K. Muthu<\/strong> (Step-son, with <strong>Padmavathy<\/strong>) and <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/kanimozhi\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Kanimozhi<\/strong><\/a> (Step-daughter, with <strong>Rajathi<\/strong>, Politician.)<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-8483 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-Step-Son.jpg\" alt=\"Dayalu Ammal's Step-Son, M. K. Muthu\" width=\"369\" height=\"336\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-Step-Son.jpg 369w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-Step-Son-300x273.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 369px) 100vw, 369px\" \/><\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_8484\" style=\"width: 383px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8484\" class=\"wp-image-8484\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammals-Step-Daughter.jpg\" alt=\"Dayalu Ammal's Step-Daughter, Kanimozhi\" width=\"373\" height=\"448\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammals-Step-Daughter.jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammals-Step-Daughter-250x300.jpg 250w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 373px) 100vw, 373px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-8484\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Dayalu Ammal&#8217;s Step-Daughter, Kanimozhi<\/p><\/div>\n<p>Her son\u00a0<strong>M.K Stalin<\/strong> became<strong> M.\u00a0Karunanidhi&#8217;s political successor\u00a0<\/strong>after\u00a02016\u00a0assembly elections.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_8486\" style=\"width: 442px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8486\" class=\" wp-image-8486\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Son-.jpg\" alt=\"Dayalu Ammal With Her Son M.K Stalin\" width=\"432\" height=\"561\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Son-.jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Son--231x300.jpg 231w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 432px) 100vw, 432px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-8486\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Dayalu Ammal With Her Son M.K Stalin<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Controversy\"><\/span><span id=\"Controversies\" class=\"ez-toc-section\" style=\"color: #800080\">Controversy<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>In 2015, Dayalu and 18 others including <strong>DMK MP Kanimozhi<\/strong> and <strong>former\u00a0Telecom Minister A Raja<\/strong> faced a trial in the case in which <strong>Enforcement Directorate (ED)<\/strong> alleged that <strong>\u20b9200 crore<\/strong> illegal gratification was routed to Kalaignar TV through an indirect way by promoters of <strong>Swan Telecom Pvt Ltd<\/strong> <strong>(STPL).<\/strong> Her doctor stated that the possibility of her involvement in the\u00a0<strong>money laundering case<\/strong>\u00a0was impossible as she has been suffering from <strong>Alzheimer<\/strong> and was not well for many years. In the year 2017, all the accused along with Dayalu were <strong>acquitted<\/strong> of the money laundering case by a <strong>special court\u00a0of CBI<\/strong>.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_8492\" style=\"width: 293px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8492\" class=\" wp-image-8492\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-Faced-Trial-in-2G-Scam-Controversy.jpg\" alt=\"Dayalu Ammal Faced Trial in 2G Scam Controversy\" width=\"283\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-Faced-Trial-in-2G-Scam-Controversy.jpg 583w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-Faced-Trial-in-2G-Scam-Controversy-219x300.jpg 219w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 283px) 100vw, 283px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-8492\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Dayalu Ammal Faced Trial in 2G Scam Controversy<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"SalaryNet_WorthMoney_Factor\"><\/span><span id=\"SalaryNet_Worth\" class=\"ez-toc-section\" style=\"color: #800080\">Salary\/Net Worth\/<strong>Money Factor<\/strong><\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>She earned \u20b964 lakh\/year (as of 2011) and has a total worth of\u00a0\u20b915.34 crore (Movable, as of 2011). She owns land in Tiruvallur District and also Dayalu Ammal Trust owns land at Madakulam Village in Madurai District. She has a 60% share in Kalignar TV and owns jewelry\u00a0worth\u00a0\u20b913 lakh.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Facts\"><\/span><span id=\"Facts\" class=\"ez-toc-section\" style=\"color: #800080\">Facts<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>She follows Hinduism.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>She loves cooking and often tries her hand at new dishes.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In 2014, <strong>Kanimozhi<\/strong> was charged\u00a0in the <strong>2G spectrum allocation case<\/strong> for co-conspiracy where <strong>Dayalu<\/strong> was produced as a <strong>prosecution witness<\/strong> by CBI.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_8503\" style=\"width: 670px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8503\" class=\" wp-image-8503\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Step-Daughter-Kanimozhi-.jpg\" alt=\"Dayalu Ammal With Her Step Daughter, Kanimozhi\" width=\"660\" height=\"477\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Step-Daughter-Kanimozhi-.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Step-Daughter-Kanimozhi--300x217.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Step-Daughter-Kanimozhi--768x556.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 660px) 100vw, 660px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-8503\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Dayalu Ammal With Her Step Daughter, Kanimozhi<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>She was diagnosed with\u00a0<strong>Alzheimer<\/strong>, <strong>Sjogren<\/strong>, <strong>Anemia<\/strong>, and other age-related diseases in the mid-<strong>1980&#8217;s<\/strong>. She has been suffering from these diseases since then.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Her son &#8216;<strong>Azhagiri<\/strong>&#8216; shares a very close bond with Dayalu among his siblings.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_8493\" style=\"width: 677px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8493\" class=\" wp-image-8493\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Son-1.jpg\" alt=\"Dayalu Ammal With Her Son, Azhagiri\" width=\"667\" height=\"437\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Son-1.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Son-1-300x197.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dayalu-Ammal-With-Her-Son-1-768x503.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-8493\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Dayalu Ammal With Her Son, Azhagiri<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<div class=\"489bcfb86580b123547338c91db0eff2\" data-index=\"3\" style=\"float: none; margin:3px 0 3px 0; text-align:center;\">\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\"\r\n     style=\"display:block\"\r\n     data-ad-format=\"autorelaxed\"\r\n     data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-6769524711517462\"\r\n     data-ad-slot=\"2473600074\"><\/ins>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"font-size: 0px; height: 0px; line-height: 0px; margin: 0; padding: 0; clear: both;\"><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Dayalu Ammal\u00a0is famous for being the Wife of Tamil Nadu\u2019s former Chief Minister and DMK Chief, M Karunanidhi.\u00a0She got married to Karunanidhi at a very young age, after the death of his first wife; becoming his second wife.\u00a0Check out Dayalu Ammal Wiki, Age, Husband, Childre, Family,\u00a0 Controversy, Biography &amp; More. Biography\/Wiki She is a 86 years old widow of\u00a0M.\u00a0Karunanidhi. Born in the\u00a0Year 1936 in\u00a0Tamil Nadu, India. She is a businesswoman. She was just 12 years old when she got married to\u00a0M.\u00a0Karunanidhi. Family, Husband In 1946, she tied the knot with\u00a0M.\u00a0Karunanidhi.\u00a0 The couple was blessed with four children. She has 3 <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":17,"featured_media":8469,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[2],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/8434"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/17"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=8434"}],"version-history":[{"count":3,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/8434\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":8511,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/8434\/revisions\/8511"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/8469"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=8434"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=8434"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=8434"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/a